.TH "vmw_bo_dirty_add" 9 "vmw_bo_dirty_add" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_bo_dirty_add \- Add a dirty-tracking user to a buffer object
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_bo_dirty_add
.BI "(struct vmw_buffer_object *vbo "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vbo" 12
The buffer object
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function registers a dirty-tracking user to a buffer object.
A user can be for example a resource or a vma in a special user-space
mapping.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success, -ENOMEM on memory allocation failure.
